   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE GOD'S HISTORY IN TIME</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>GEN.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>1:1 REV.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>20:15 2 RESTORING THE JUDGED UNIVERSE</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>AND CREATING MAN OUTLINE Restoring the judged universe Gen 1:2-25: The earth was waste and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep the issue of God's judgment upon His original creation v. 2a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Spirit of God was brooding upon the face of the waters v. 2b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God restored the light to divide the light from the darkness, calling the light Day and the darkness Night, on the first day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>3-5.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>God made the firmament in the midst of the waters to divide the waters under the firmament from the waters above the firmament; God called the firmament Heaven, on the second day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>6-8.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>God gathered the waters under the heavens together unto one place and caused the dry land to appear; God called the dry land Earth and the gathering together of the waters Seas, on the third day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>God caused the earth to put forth grass, herbs, and fruit trees, on the third day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>11-13.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>God restored the lights in heaven to divide the day from the night, for signs, for seasons, for days and years, and for lights in heaven to give light upon the earth: two great lights the greater to rule the day and the lesser to rule the night and stars, on the fourth day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>14-19.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>God caused the waters to swarm with swarms of living creatures, and birds to fly above the earth in heaven and multiply on earth, on the fifth day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>20-23.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>God caused the earth to bring forth living creatures: cattle, creeping things, and beasts of the earth, on the sixth day vv.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Creating man Gen 1:26 2:25:</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>God's history in time with man objectively</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Gen 1:26 Mal 4:6 God created man in His image, after His likeness, on the sixth day Gen 1:26-31: To express Him in person vv.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>26a, 27.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To represent Him in office vv.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>26b, 28.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Jehovah God formed man of the dust of the ground for man's body and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life for man's spirit ; and man became a living soul Gen 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Jehovah God put man in the garden of Eden in front of two trees Gen 2:8-9: The tree of life, signifying God in Christ as life to man, to be taken by man Rev 2:7b; 22:2, 14, 19.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The tree of the knowledge of good and evil, signifying Satan as the origin of death Heb 2:14 , to be prohibited from being eaten by man Gen 2:17; 3:3.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>With a river, in the flow of which are gold, bdellium, and onyx stone Gen 2:10-12.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Jehovah God built a woman with the rib of Adam as his wife to match him as his counterpart, signifying that the church was constituted with the resurrection life of Christ to be His counterpart Gen 2:18-24; Eph 5:23-32.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>God rested on the seventh day after He finished all His work which He created and made Gen 2:1-3.</S>
   </TEXT>
